Source: pda-kernel-dkms
Maintainer: Dirk Hutter <hutter@compeng.uni-frankfurt.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), dkms

Package: pda-kernel-dkms
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: adduser, ${misc:Depends}
Description: dkms source for the PDA uio_pci_dma driver
 The Portable Driver Architecture (PDA) is a microdriver library for
 programming Linux PCI drivers in the userspace.
 .
 This package provides the dkms source code for the PDA's uio_pci_dma
 kernel module.
 Kernel source or headers are required to compile these modules.
